# clj-mallet

Clojure wrapper code to programmatically call the MALLET API to do LDA
topic modeling.  For example, we may wish to run LDA directly against
text records in a database without messing around with the filesystem.

## Usage

(def corpus {"Doc1" "Foo bar baz cattle snow machine",
             "Doc2" "Snoopy snoopy snoopy snoopy", ...})
(def instances (clj-mallet.instances/get-instance-list corpus))
(def T 50)
(def numsamp 500)
(def topicmodel (clj-mallet.lda/run-lda instances T numsamp))
(clj-mallet.lda/write-topic-word topicmodel "mycorpus.topics")

